---
description: Auto-build Space Dust after code changes
alwaysApply: true
globs: ["*.cpp", "*.h", "CMakeLists.txt", "*.cmake"]
---

After any code generation or file changes in the Space Dust project:

1. Automatically run the complete build script that handles everything:
   cd <project-root>
   & .\build-and-launch.ps1
   (Do NOT pass -NoLaunch; Ableton must launch on every successful build.)

   This script will:
   - Clean and rebuild the project
   - Copy the VST3 to custom folder
   - Wait 2 seconds for filesystem to settle
   - Automatically launch Ableton Live (if not already running)
   - Provide clear success/error messages at each step

   If the build script doesn't exist, fall back to manual commands:
   cd <project-root>
   Remove-Item -Recurse -Force build -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
   mkdir build
   cd build
   cmake .. -G "Visual Studio 17 2022" -A x64
   cmake --build . --config Release
   cd ..
   $customVST3 = "$env:USERPROFILE\Documents\Ableton\User Library\VST3"
   if (-not (Test-Path $customVST3)) { New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path $customVST3 -Force | Out-Null }
   $sourceVST3 = "build\SpaceDust_artefacts\Release\VST3\Space Dust.vst3"
   if (Test-Path $sourceVST3) {
       Copy-Item -Path $sourceVST3 -Destination $customVST3 -Recurse -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
       Write-Host "✓ Copied Space Dust.vst3" -ForegroundColor Green
   }
   Start-Sleep -Seconds 2
   if (Test-Path ".\launch-ableton.ps1") { & .\launch-ableton.ps1 }

3. If there are compile errors, diagnose them using the juce-docs MCP tool, fix the code, and retry the build automatically.

Prioritize real-time safe audio code and latest JUCE 8 practices.